RunUps

Runup is the maximum height of the water observed above a reference sea level. Runups can be determined by the tsunami magnitude and tsunami intensity.

The following plots show the different values for both attributes for all countries throughout the years, and a scatter plot is used to detect relationship among them.

Magnitude and Intensity



Damage Index Interpretation:


0. Extreme (~$25 million or more)

1. Limited (<$1 million)

2. Moderate (~ 1𝑡𝑜 5 million)

3. Severe (~> 5𝑡𝑜 24 million)



Validity Index Interpretation:


0. Definite Tsunami

1. Questionable Tsunami

2. Very Doubtful Tsunami

3. Probable Tsunami

4. Event that only caused a seiche or disturbance in an inland river
